revenue_recognition.description: Investment transactions are accounted for on a trade date basis. Interest is recorded using the effective interest method. Dividend income is recorded on the ex-dividend date.

valuation_of_investments.description: Investments are valued at fair value according to a hierarchy (Level 1, 2, 3) based on market observability. Level 1 uses quoted prices in active markets, Level 2 uses observable inputs, and Level 3 uses unobservable inputs.

foreign_currency_translation.description: Foreign-denominated assets and liabilities are translated at the exchange rate on the valuation date. Income and expenses are translated at the rate on the transaction date. Changes are included in net realized and unrealized gains/losses.

consolidation_policies.description: The fund operates under a master-feeder structure. The financial statements reflect only the Master Fund and do not consolidate feeder funds. No subsidiaries are consolidated.

strategies.description: The fund uses a diversified portfolio of equity, currency, fixed-income, and commodity-linked instruments, both long and short, to pursue systematic trading strategies. This includes the use of derivatives to follow price trends and mitigate overextension of trends.
The fund employs futures, forward foreign currency exchange contracts, interest rate swaps, and credit default swaps. These are not used for accounting hedges but are part of its core strategy.
The fund uses a fair value hierarchy (Level 13) based on market observability to classify and value financial instruments.
Counterparty risk is mitigated through master netting agreements and margin posting for OTC derivatives.
The fund holds and trades foreign currencies and forward contracts, and recognizes gains/losses based on translation at prevailing rates.

fields.income_taxes: The fund generally is not subject to U.S. federal income tax on trading gains. U.S. source dividends and interest may be subject to withholding tax. Foreign income may also be subject to tax in its source jurisdiction. The General Partner evaluates tax positions using the 'more-likely-than-not' threshold and concluded no uncertain tax benefits or liabilities exist as of year-end.
fields.fair_value_measurements: Investments are measured at fair value using a three-level hierarchy: Level 1 (quoted prices in active markets), Level 2 (observable inputs), and Level 3 (unobservable inputs). Derivatives, equities, debt securities, and other assets are classified accordingly. Valuation techniques include market quotes, pricing services, and models adjusted for liquidity or credit risk.

Audit report.title_of_the_report: Report of Independent Registered Public Accounting Firm
Audit report.addressee: To the Partners and Board of Directors of AQR Managed Futures Fund, L.P.
Audit report.introduction_paragraph: We have audited the accompanying statement of assets and liabilities, including the schedule of investments, of AQR Managed Futures Fund, L.P. as of December 31, 2024, and the related statements of operations, changes in partners capital, and cash flows for the year then ended, including the related notes.
Audit report.managements_responsibility: Management is responsible for the preparation and fair presentation of the financial statements in conformity with U.S. generally accepted accounting principles, and for the design, implementation, and maintenance of internal control relevant to the preparation and fair presentation of financial statements.
Audit report.auditors_responsibility: Our responsibility is to express an opinion on these financial statements based on our audit. We conducted our audit in accordance with the standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States). Those standards require that we plan and perform the audit to obtain reasonable assurance about whether the financial statements are free of material misstatement.
Audit report.opinion_paragraph: In our opinion, the financial statements referred to above present fairly, in all material respects, the financial position of AQR Managed Futures Fund, L.P. at December 31, 2024, and the results of its operations, changes in partners capital, and its cash flows for the year then ended in conformity with U.S. generally accepted accounting principles.
Audit report.basis_for_opinion: We are a public accounting firm registered with the PCAOB and are required to be independent with respect to AQR Managed Futures Fund, L.P. in accordance with U.S. federal securities laws and the applicable rules and regulations of the Securities and Exchange Commission and the PCAOB.
